  "final_text": "The variable `uart_buf_count` doesn't exist in **any** ELF or source file in this fixture tree. Let me confirm what's actually running on the flash by resolving the callstack against the VCP-ECHO ELF:\nNo problem \u2014 leaving it here. To summarize the state:\n\n- **Probe pinning needed:** with both probes attached, prefix debug commands with `STM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514` (the L476RG).\n- **Flash \u2260 descriptor default:** the board is running **VCP-ECHO**, not BLINKY, so pass the VCP-ECHO ELF explicitly.\n- **`uart_buf_count` doesn't exist** in any ELF or source in this tree, so the check can't pass as written.\n\nOnce you tell me the right variable name (or the right firmware), the one-liner is:\n\n```bash\nSTM32_PROGRAMMER_DEFAULT_SN=066DFF485754727567021514 stm32 debug check-variable \\\n  --at main --var <name> --expected 0 \\\n  Projects/NUCLEO-L476RG/Examples/PWR/VCP-ECHO/STM32CubeIDE/Debug/VCP-ECHO.elf\n```\n\n(For VCP-ECHO as-is, the only candidate in `main` is `byte`, initialized to 0.)"
